result.execSummary:
Brett Charles Douglas was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Brett Charles Douglas was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Letter to Governor of WI with copy of Extradition Consent and Fugitive Complaint.

Defendant Brett Charles Douglas in court, in custody.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court informs the defendant he's being held on a Warrant out of Winona County, Minnesota, explains Extradition process and advises defendant of rights.  Defendant waives extradition.  Waiver of Extradition filed with Court.  Court finds defendant's waiver of extradition done knowingly & voluntarily and remands him to Pepin County Sheriff's Department to forthwith be delivered to State of Minneosta.
